09/01/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- The new government was sworn in on Thursday (January 8th) at a ceremony in Athens attended by the head of the Hellenic Orthodox Church Archbishop Ieronymos II, President Karolos Papoulias and Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis. 
After the ceremony, the new cabinet gathered for its first session, at which Karamanlis presided. 
He told the ministers he expects little talking and much work and said the priorities are the national interest, security, the economy, education, healthcare and the consequences of the global financial crisis. 
Karamanlis urged the ministers to limit costs and propose bold initiatives to cut red tape and improve transparency. 
(RIA Novosti, News In, ERT, Eleftheros Typos - 08/01/09)
